<p>For help related to this form, see the box below</p>
<br>
<%= form_for Product.new, validate: true do |f| %>
    <div class="row" id="normal_form">
      <div class="input-field col s12">
        <%= f.select(:category_id, Category.select)%>
        <%= f.label :category %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row" id="normal_form">
      <div class="input-field col s12">
        <%= f.label :title %>
        <%= f.text_field :title, data: { validation: 'required'} %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row" id="normal_form">
      <div class="input-field col s12">
        <%= f.label :description %>
        <%= f.text_area :description, class: 'materialize-textarea', data: { validation: 'required'} %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row" id="normal_form">
      <div class="input-field col s12">
        <%= f.label :company %>
        <%= f.text_field :company, data: { validation: 'required'} %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row" id="normal_form">

      <div class="input-field col s12">
        <%= f.label :tags %>
        <%= f.text_field :tags, data: { role: 'materialtags'}, data: { validation: 'required'}%>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row" id="normal_form">
      <div class="input-field col s12">
        <%= f.label :product_images %>
        <%= f.text_area :product_images, class: 'materialize-textarea'%>
      </div>
    </div>


    <button class="btn waves-effect waves-light" type="submit" name="action">Submit Product Description
      <i class="material-icons right">send</i>
    </button>
<% end %>
<br>
<h2 class="flow-text title-imp center">Form Help</h2>

<div class="row">
  <ul class="collapsible" data-collapsible="accordion">
    <li>
      <div class="collapsible-header">Title</div>
      <div class="collapsible-body"><p>Make sure the title correctly describes the name of the product.
      Title is used by search engine to find your product</p></div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="collapsible-header">Description</div>
      <div class="collapsible-body"><p>Description should be succinct and clearly describe the product.
      There is no length restriction but you should make sure to divide the description in paragraphs</p></div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="collapsible-header">Company</div>
      <div class="collapsible-body"><p>Make sure the company is relevant and it appears on google search</p></div>
    </li>

    <li>
      <div class="collapsible-header">Tags</div>
      <div class="collapsible-body"><p>Tags are words which describe the product. Put atleast one tag which describes your product. Maximum tags for
      a product is 6. The rest will be ignored by search engine so make sure they are close to the product description</p></div>
    </li>

    <li>
      <div class="collapsible-header">Product Images</div>
      <div class="collapsible-body"><p>Put atleast 4 product images for your product. If left blank, images won't
      be shown. Each image should be a link and should either end with .jpg or.png and separated with a comma Eg:- <br>
        http://www.example.com/example1.jpg, http://www.example.com/example2.jpg, http://www.example.com/example1.jpg</p></div>
    </li>
  </ul>

</div>

<script type="text/javascript" charset="utf-8">
  $('#product_category_id').material_select();
  $('#product_tags').materialtags();
  $('.collapsible').collapsible({
    accordion : false // A setting that changes the collapsible behavior to expandable instead of the default accordion style
  });
  $.validate({
    form : "#<%= action_name.to_s %>_<%= controller_name.singularize.to_s %>"
  });

</script>

